From: Pawan Gupta <pawan.kumar.gupta@linux.intel.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Jun 2024 21:17:21 -0700
Subject: x86/its: Add support for ITS-safe return thunk
Git-commit: a75bf27fe41abe658c53276a0c486c4bf9adecfc
Patch-mainline: v6.15-rc7
References: bsc#1242006 CVE-2024-28956

RETs in the lower half of cacheline may be affected by ITS bug,
specifically when the RSB-underflows. Use ITS-safe return thunk for such
RETs.

RETs that are not patched:

- RET in retpoline sequence does not need to be patched, because the
  sequence itself fills an RSB before RET.
- RET in Call Depth Tracking (CDT) thunks __x86_indirect_{call|jump}_thunk
  and call_depth_return_thunk are not patched because CDT by design
  prevents RSB-underflow.
- RETs in .init section are not reachable after init.
- RETs that are explicitly marked safe with ANNOTATE_UNRET_SAFE.

Signed-off-by: Pawan Gupta <pawan.kumar.gupta@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Dave Hansen <dave.hansen@linux.intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Josh Poimboeuf <jpoimboe@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Alexandre Chartre <alexandre.chartre@oracle.com>
Acked-by: Nikolay Borisov <nik.borisov@suse.com>
---
 arch/x86/kernel/vmlinux.lds.S |    1 +
 arch/x86/lib/retpoline.S      |    2 ++
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/x86/kernel/vmlinux.lds.S
+++ b/arch/x86/kernel/vmlinux.lds.S
@@ -440,6 +440,7 @@ INIT_PER_CPU(irq_stack_union);
 . = ASSERT(__x86_indirect_thunk_rax & 0x20, "__x86_indirect_thunk_rax not in second half of cacheline");
 . = ASSERT(((__x86_indirect_thunk_rcx - __x86_indirect_thunk_rax) % 64) == 0, "Indirect thunks are not cacheline apart");
 . = ASSERT(__x86_indirect_its_thunk_array == __x86_indirect_thunk_rax, "Gap in ITS thunk array");
+. = ASSERT(__x86_return_thunk & 0x20, "its_return_thunk not in second half of cacheline");
 #endif
 
 #endif /* CONFIG_X86_32 */
--- a/arch/x86/lib/retpoline.S
+++ b/arch/x86/lib/retpoline.S
@@ -220,6 +220,8 @@ ENTRY(entry_untrain_ret)
 ENDPROC(entry_untrain_ret)
 __EXPORT_THUNK(entry_untrain_ret)
 
+.align 64, 0xcc
+.skip 32, 0xcc
 ENTRY(__x86_return_thunk)
 	UNWIND_HINT_FUNC
 	ALTERNATIVE_2 "jmp __ret", "call srso_safe_ret", X86_FEATURE_SRSO, \
